author: wn.com
title: Clinton to detail sweeping plan to rein in Wall Street
text: WASHINGTON (Reuters) - U.S. Democratic presidential candidate Hillary Clinton on Thursday will unveil a sweeping plan to curb what she has said are the abuses of Wall Street, proposing everything from raising the fines that can be levied by regulators to requiring executives to bear some of those costs.
